        <abstract> 
<p>Hopes to get Asa Gray’s review of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> republished.</p> 
            <p>Argues for single origin of mammals.</p>
            <p>Encloses two phylogenetic diagrams indicating possible descent of mammals.</p>
            <p>Comments on rodents, marsupials, and dingo in Australia,</p>
            <p>and on a paper on the survival of stumps as a result of root grafting.</p>
            <p>Argues that man had a single progenitor and consists of a single species.</p>
            <p>Comments on destruction of non-white races.</p>
            <p>Discusses introduction of rodents to islands by man.</p>
        </abstract>
